# parse()

**Instance Method**

Starts the event-driven parsing operation.

## Declaration

```swift
func parse() -> Bool
```

## Return Value

[doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/Swift/true] if the parsing operation succeeds; [doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/Swift/false] if an error occurs or if the parsing operation aborts.

## Parsing

- **abortParsing()**: Stops the parser object.
- **parserError**: An [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/NSError] object from which you can obtain information about a parsing error.
